The deals were ground out over five days of bargaining at a Geneva conference of more than 100 trade ministers. The deal on a partial intellectual property waiver, to allow developing countries to produce and export Covid19 vaccines, has also been passed, after two-years of negotiations. The WTO's Director-General, Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala, says the package of agreements they have reached will make a difference to the lives of people around the world. “The outcomes demonstrate that the WTO is in fact capable of responding to emergencies of our time”, she said. Okonjo-Iweala said the outcomes show the world that WTO members can come together to address problems of the global commands.  --BBC-- 